The investigation into the wealth of former President Soeharto and his family is ongoing, with officials targeting the Soeharto family regardless of who is involved in any wrongdoing.
Senior officials, including ministers and governors, are under scrutiny for their wealth accumulated through questionable business practices.
Soedjono, a lawyer, emphasized the importance of defending truth and justice in accordance with ethical standards.
Indonesian Attorney General Soedjono C. Atmonegoro confirmed the investigation, urging the public to provide information on officials' wealth.
Calls for accountability and forgiveness towards Soeharto's contributions to Indonesia have sparked debates on legal actions and asset recovery.
